08/04/2010
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Anna-Maria Borissova, an endocrinologist and a professor at the Medical University in Sofia, has been chosen as next health minister, Prime Minister Boyko Borisov announced Wednesday (April 7th).
She takes up the post vacated by Bozhidar Nanev, who resigned after prosecutors indicted him in connection with medicine supply deals that caused about 1.75m euros in losses to the state.
(bTV, Darik, Dnevnik, Mediapool - 07/04/10)
